-- Jeamland line editor
-- --------------------
-- ~c[line]        -- Change a line (or last line).
-- ~d[range]       -- Delete a line (or last line).
-- ~h              -- This help page.
-- ~i<line>        -- Insert above a line.
-- ~j<line>        -- Join <line> to the line after it.
-- ~l[sl[,el]]     -- List entered lines so far or list lines from sl to el
--		      or last 'more-length' lines.
-- ~m[sl[,el]] tl  -- Move a line or block of lines to before tl.
-- ~o[[no]opt]     -- List or change options.
-- ~q              -- Abort.
-- ~r		   -- Recover Editor buffer.
-- ~s[line][^]s^r  -- Search for text 's' and replace with 'r' on a particular
--                    line. Line is optional, as is the first ^ character.
-- .               -- Save and Exit / Leave insert mode.
-- 
-- A range is a comma delimited list of ranges of numbers (eg. 1-4,7)
-- Either end of a range may be ommited, eg. 4- selects all lines from 4
-- onwards.
-- To type a line beginning with a ~ character, prefix it with a \
